Rating: 4
I took some liberty with this recipe, but I ended up with the best pot pie I've ever had, so I thought I would write a review. Instead of turkey, I used the substantial leftovers of a (home-raised) goose that I had roasted a couple of nights before. So, I also used goose fat (instead of butter to cook the vegetables in) and goose broth. I omitted the carrots (didn't have any on hand), almost doubled the amount of peas, and used potatoes instead of parsnips. I'm quite sure that I added more than 4 cups of goose meat, and so it looked like I actually needed more sauce so I whipped up a little more gravy (goose fat, flour, goose broth) and added it into the mixture. Glad I did. The results were amazing. I will say that a little extra "gravy" when baking the pot pie is good, as the biscuits seemed to soak up a lot of the liquid. Also, I ended up with about twice the vegetable and meat filling that I needed for one deep dish skillet, and I had enough biscuit batter to bake an extra three biscuits. I froze the remainder of the filling, because I'm quite sure I'll be making this again, very soon. And again. And again... Summary: Very flavorful filling, perfect biscuits, adaptable recipe.

