This was the best pot pie. Barefoot contessa has a good one, but this beats it! I put in 3 c. broth only. I added about three extra tablespoons flour to make it thicker. Would do this at the roux stage. I wouldn't add the extra 1/2 tsp salt with the veggies. The bouillon has enough flavor. I used 6 ramekins of different sizes. I only put in enough turkey into each serving that would be tasty. Tent the ramekins with foil as soon as they get a little brown, this makes beautiful brown biscuits. I used only mushrooms, carrots, turkey and onions. A keeper!

