My boyfriend and I really enjoyed this recipe. I cooked a 13 lb turkey for two of people so it was a good way to use up the enormous amount of leftovers. We followed the recipe pretty closely making some minor adjustments for ingredients we were lacking (no parsnip; used dried thyme; substituted heavy cream with a touch of lemon juice for buttermilk). We didn't have any large casserole dishes so we baked it in the same pan we cooked the filling in. This had the additional benefit of dirtying fewer dishes. Unlike other reviewers I did not find the sauce/gravy to be too thin. Most of the stock was absorbed/evaporated after baking leaving the vegetables with a hearty coating. I actually prefer my pot pies to be "saucier" so when I reheated leftovers I added a small amount of water. That (in my opinion) made the consistency perfect! I imagine the surface area/volume ratio of the baking dish significantly affects how much the sauce thickens so that might be something to consider.

